name: glacier
definition: a slowly moving mass of ice

name: basin (natural depression)
definition: a natural depression in the surface of the land often with a lake at the bottom of it

name: bed (natural depression)
definition: a depression forming the ground under a body of water

name: crater
definition: a bowl-shaped depression formed by the impact of a meteorite or bomb

name: hole (natural depression)
definition: a depression hollowed out of solid matter

name: lowland
definition: low level country

name: valley
definition: a long depression in the surface of the land that usually contains a river

name: highland
definition: elevated (e.g., mountainous) land

name: hill
definition: a local and well-defined elevation of the land

name: mountain
definition: a land mass that projects well above its surroundings; higher than a hill

name: promontory
definition: a natural elevation (especially a rocky one that juts out into the sea)

name: ridge (natural elevation)
definition: a long narrow natural elevation or striation

name: seashore
definition: the shore of a sea or ocean

name: descent
definition: a downward slope or bend

name: axis (line)
definition: a straight line through a body or figure that satisfies certain conditions

name: great circle
definition: a circular line on the surface of a sphere formed by intersecting it with a plane passing through the center

name: isogram
definition: a line drawn on a map connecting points having the same numerical value of some variable

name: latitude (line)
definition: an imaginary line around the Earth parallel to the equator

name: line of force
definition: an imaginary line in a field of force; direction of the line at any point is the direction of the force at that point

name: air lane
definition: a designated route followed by airplanes in flying from one airport to another

name: direction
definition: a line leading to a place or point

name: trail (path)
definition: a track or mark left by something that has passed

name: water line
definition: a line marking the level reached by a body of water

name: col
definition: a pass between mountain peaks

name: beginning
definition: the place where something begins, where it springs into being

name: celestial point
definition: a point in the heavens (on the celestial sphere)

name: center (point)
definition: a point equidistant from the ends of a line or the extremities of a figure

name: canthus
definition: either of the corners of the eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet

name: geographic point
definition: a point on the surface of the Earth

name: military position
definition: a point occupied by troops for tactical reasons

name: post (position)
definition: the position where someone (as a guard or sentry) stands or is assigned to stand

name: site (position)
definition: physical position in relation to the surroundings

name: topographic point
definition: a point located with respect to surface features of some region

name: boundary
definition: the line or plane indicating the limit or extent of something

name: end (extremity)
definition: either extremity of something that has length

name: extreme point
definition: the point located farthest from the middle of something

name: limit (extremity)
definition: as far as something can go

name: crust (layer)
definition: the outer layer of the Earth

name: snow
definition: a layer of snowflakes (white crystals of frozen water) covering the ground

name: stratum
definition: one of several parallel layers of material arranged one on top of another (such as a layer of tissue or cells in an organism or a layer of sedimentary rock)

name: combat zone (zone)
definition: a military area where combat forces operate

name: anchorage
definition: place for vessels to anchor

name: center (area)
definition: an area that is approximately central within some larger region

name: resort area
definition: an area where many people go for recreation

name: retreat
definition: a place of privacy; a place affording peace and quiet

name: scene (area)
definition: the place where some action occurs

name: section (area)
definition: a distinct region or subdivision of a territorial or political area or community or group of people

name: space (area)
definition: an area reserved for some particular purpose

name: administrative district
definition: a district defined for administrative purposes

name: city district
definition: a district of a town or city

name: development
definition: a district that has been developed to serve some purpose

name: jurisdiction
definition: in law; the territory within which power can be exercised

name: residential district
definition: a district where people live; occupied primarily by private residences

name: country (geographical area)
definition: an area outside of cities and towns

name: environment
definition: the area in which something exists or lives

name: field (geographical area)
definition: a geographic region (land or sea) under which something valuable is found

name: hemisphere
definition: half of the terrestrial globe

name: place (geographical area)
definition: any area set aside for a particular purpose

name: river basin
definition: the entire geographical area drained by a river and its tributaries; an area characterized by all runoff being conveyed to the same outlet

name: settlement
definition: an area where a group of families live together

name: tract
definition: an extended area of land

name: urban area
definition: a geographical area constituting a city or town

name: wilderness
definition: a wild and uninhabited area left in its natural condition

name: zone (geographical area)
definition: any of the regions of the surface of the Earth loosely divided according to latitude or longitude

name: angle (space)
definition: the space between two lines or planes that intersect; the inclination of one line to another; measured in degrees or radians

name: cavity
definition: space that is surrounded by something

name: compartment (space)
definition: a space into which an area is subdivided

name: enclosure (space)
definition: a naturally enclosed space

name: expanse
definition: a wide and open space or area as of surface or land or sky

name: opening (space)
definition: an open or empty space in or between things

name: handle
definition: the appendage to an object that is designed to be held in order to use or move it

name: accessory (component)
definition: a supplementary component that improves capability

name: addition (component)
definition: a component that is added to something to improve it

name: hardware (component)
definition: (computer science) the mechanical, magnetic, electronic, and electrical components making up a computer system

name: heating element
definition: the component of a heater or range that transforms fuel or electricity into heat

name: ingredient
definition: a component of a mixture or compound

name: module (component)
definition: a self-contained component (unit or item) that is used in combination with other components

name: piece of leather
definition: a separate part consisting of leather

name: bend (section)
definition: curved segment (of a road or river or railroad track etc.)

name: straightaway
definition: a straight segment of a roadway or racecourse

name: antiquity
definition: an artifact surviving from the past

name: article (artifact)
definition: one of a class of artifacts

name: block (artifact)
definition: a solid piece of something (usually having flat rectangular sides)

name: building material
definition: material used for constructing buildings

name: commodity
definition: articles of commerce

name: covering (artifact)
definition: an artifact that covers something else (usually to protect or shelter or conceal it)

name: creation
definition: an artifact that has been brought into existence by someone

name: decoration
definition: something used to beautify

name: excavation
definition: a hole in the ground made by excavating

name: fabric
definition: artifact made by weaving or felting or knitting or crocheting natural or synthetic fibers

name: airfield
definition: a place where planes take off and land

name: athletic facility
definition: a facility for athletic events

name: communication system (facility)
definition: facility consisting of the physical plants and equipment for disseminating information

name: course (facility)
definition: facility consisting of a circumscribed area of land or water laid out for a sport

name: depository
definition: a facility where things can be deposited for storage or safekeeping

name: military installation
definition: any facility servicing military forces

name: range (facility)
definition: a place for shooting (firing or driving) projectiles of various kinds

name: source
definition: a facility where something is available

name: station (facility)
definition: a facility equipped with special equipment and personnel for a particular purpose

name: transportation system
definition: a facility consisting of the means and equipment necessary for the movement of passengers or goods

name: utility
definition: a facility composed of one or more pieces of equipment connected to or part of a structure and designed to provide a service such as heat or electricity or water or sewage disposal

name: fixture
definition: an object firmly fixed in place (especially in a household)

name: float (artifact)
definition: something that floats on the surface of water

name: instrumentality
definition: an artifact (or system of artifacts) that is instrumental in accomplishing some end

name: layer (artifact)
definition: single thickness of usually some homogeneous substance

name: line (artifact)
definition: something (as a cord or rope) that is long and thin and flexible

name: marker (artifact)
definition: some conspicuous object used to distinguish or mark something

name: opening (artifact)
definition: a vacant or unobstructed space that is man-made

name: padding
definition: artifact consisting of soft or resilient material used to fill or give shape or protect or add comfort

name: paving
definition: material used to pave an area

name: plaything
definition: an artifact designed to be played with

name: sheet (artifact)
definition: a flat artifact that is thin relative to its length and width

name: sphere (artifact)
definition: any spherically shaped artifact

name: strip (artifact)
definition: artifact consisting of a narrow flat piece of material

name: structure
definition: a thing constructed; a complex entity constructed of many parts

name: surface (artifact)
definition: the outer boundary of an artifact or a material layer constituting or resembling such a boundary

name: thing
definition: an artifact

name: track (artifact)
definition: a pair of parallel rails providing a runway for wheels

name: way
definition: any artifact consisting of a road or path affording passage from one place to another

name: weight (artifact)
definition: an artifact that is heavy

name: cell (living thing)
definition: (biology) the basic structural and functional unit of all organisms; they may exist as independent units of life (as in monads) or may form colonies or tissues as in higher plants and animals

name: organism
definition: a living thing that has (or can develop) the ability to act or function independently

name: human body
definition: alternative names for the body of a human being

name: chromosome
definition: a threadlike strand of DNA in the cell nucleus that carries the genes in a linear order

name: inclusion body
definition: any small intracellular body found within another (characteristic of certain diseases)

name: mass
definition: a body of matter without definite shape

name: particle
definition: a body having finite mass and internal structure but negligible dimensions

name: celestial body
definition: natural objects visible in the sky

name: covering (natural object)
definition: a natural object that covers or envelops

name: extraterrestrial object
definition: a natural object existing outside the earth and outside the earth's atmosphere

name: mechanism (natural object)
definition: a natural object resembling a machine in structure or function

name: nest (natural object)
definition: a structure in which animals lay eggs or give birth to their young

name: plant part
definition: any part of a plant or fungus

name: rock (natural object)
definition: a lump or mass of hard consolidated mineral matter

name: sample
definition: all or part of a natural object that is collected and preserved as an example of its class

name: tangle
definition: a twisted and tangled mass that is highly interwoven

name: universe
definition: everything that exists anywhere
